description_bullet: 14oz Alternating Twill Japanese Denim,100% Organic Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: TOX775106
description_paragraph:
The Toxic Avenger Deformed Denim is a 14oz alternating twill denim woven in Japan with 100% organic cotton. The Toxic Avenger is an 80s B-movie turned cult classic. Its posters boast, “The first Super-Hero…from New Jersey!” Tale as old as time: 98-pounds of “solid nerd” is a janitor at a health club in Tromaville, New Jersey. Club members bully him constantly. In one stunt, they trick him into wearing a pink tutu, and he falls into toxic waste that deforms him and gives him superhuman size and strength. He keeps the tutu, takes his mop, fights crime and pollution, takes on the nickname “Toxie,” and saves Tromaville! This Deformed Denim alternates three different weaves to echo Toxie’s mutations: a right-hand twill, a left-hand twill, and a broken twill. Wild texture ripples through the fabric. The cotton is organic with a light green interior weft, so the Toxic Avenger will know he’s not alone in his fight against filth and injustice. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, Toxie’s face embroidered on the back pocket, pink pocket bags – like his tutu – with a comic book screen print, a Natural Veg Tan with Black Foil Emboss leather patch, and metallic buttons and rivets. The Easy Guy is a high-rise tapered fit with a relaxed top block and a sharp taper from knee to hem.

 SKU: TOX775106
name: Toxic Avenger Deformed Denim

description_bullet: 15oz Unsanforized Japanese Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101100306
description_paragraph:
The True Grit Selvedge is a 15oz Unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim. Couple hairy, short-staple cotton yarns and rattly decades-old shuttle loom to get a denim grain this uneven and gritty. The brown cotton weft comes from using rare undyed natural brown cotton yarns, which gives the fabric a warm, earthy undertone. Look harder at the back of the cloth to notice different shades of brown in the weft. As cotton matures, its color changes greatly, so the varying brown hues reflect the different maturities of the cotton plants when they were harvested to make this yarn to make these jeans. Because of this, no two pairs of these will be the same and they will be unreproducible because every shade in the weft is a reflection of when each individual cotton plant was harvested. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, a Hair-On Bovine Leather patch, antique copper buttons and rivets. The Easy Guy is a high-rise tapered fit with a relaxed top block and a sharp taper from knee to hem.  This denim will shrink when soaked, so please refer to the measurement guides.

description_bullet: 23oz Unsanforized Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101034106
description_paragraph:
The King of Slub is a 23oz Unsanforized Japanese Selvedge denim with an extremely slubby uneven texture. A result of low tension weaving techniques, and the use of custom developed irregular sized “King Slub Yarn”. The King Slub Yarn was developed over a 2 year period, as standard Slub yarns could not produce such an extreme three dimensional texture. The yarn is rope dyed with indigo and due to the thickness and irregular shape of the yarn indigo absorption varies from section to section. Over time with wear, as the indigo starts to fade, a wide gradient of indigo becomes visible, and the thickness of the yarn allows for an extreme high contrast three dimensional textured fade. Other details include contrast stitching, buffalo leather patch, red selvedge ID, dark copper buttons and rivets. The Easy Guy is a relaxed tapered fit; high rise, fuller in the seat and thigh with a sharp taper from knee to hem.

description_paragraph:
The Lord of Nep Selvedge is an extremely neppy 14.5oz Japanese selvedge denim. Neppy yarns typically have a small number of small knots and fibers that appear as small imperfections in a woven fabric. But this Lord of Nep Yarn has been custom-developed to create the neppiest denim ever made with an extreme amount of knots. When woven, the denim becomes overrun with three-dimensional neps that pop like popcorn on both the front and back side of the fabric. The Lord of Nep Selvedge is woven on vintage shuttle looms and finished with a classic red-line selvedge ID. The jeans have been pre-washed to remove shrink from the fabric as the denim was too neppy to go through traditional fabric finishing processes.  Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, an ostrich leather patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets. Kakishubu dying is a traditional Japanese dye method which utilizes “Kaki” (the Japanese word for persimmon) a small orange fruit that produces an incredible range of orange and brown tones.  For this denim a deep brown dubbed “Kogare” (Japanese for burnt) was used to make up the interior weft yarns.  This denim is unsanforized, however a special Tenpi wash treatment was applied to preshrink and preserve the natural rigidness and beauty of the fabric. There is no need to pre-soak this denim, it is ready to wear from the first day.  Other details include, signature red maple leaf pocket embroidery, 10oz vegetable tanned leather patch with “Flower of Carnage” logo, white ear selvedge ID with an orange running stitch embroidery, 100% iron buttons and copper rivets.   The Easy Guy is a laid back fit with a higher rise, fuller in the seat, hips and thighs with a sharp taper from the knee to hem. 
 100% Cotton 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: NFMIJ05RT
name: Kogare Kakishibu Made in Japan 5

   NOTE  - Our estimated post soak measurement results were derived by machine hot washing and drying a single pair of jeans.  We did this to ensure maximum shrinkage.  We then collected the measurements post shrink, and  then calculated the percentage shrink rate across all measurement points.  We then applied the shrink rate percentage across all pre soak measurements and listed the results. We have found that the shrink rate was about 5%, less than typical unsanforized denims, though we suspect that some shrinkage occurred during production during the final press process which introduces steam and heat to the garment. description_bullet: 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101565606
description_paragraph:
The MIJ8 – Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim is a 16oz unsanforized Japanese selvedge denim hand dyed in Tokushima Japan, renowned worldwide for its indigo dyeing traditions. Only a handful of craftspeople in the world are trained in traditional Japanese hank dyeing. In this method, yarns are gathered into a bunch called a hank, and then dipped over and over again into a batch of natural indigo. Since the process is fully done by hand, every yard of fabric is unique. Natural indigo is created from the leaves of the indigo plant. While most indigo plants come from India, the traditional hank dye method only allows for the use of indigo grown on Japanese soil. Very little indigo is grown in Japan each year, making these jeans even more rare. Due to the lengthy fermentation process, it takes about 1 year to produce a new batch of natural Japanese indigo. The big slub yarns create a streaky irregular grain with thick cotton ridges rising out of the 3x1 twill. Check the weft to see the twill line distortion. The Unsanforized fabric avoids the standard finishing processes of heating, stretching, steaming, and singing to protect all of the natural character of the fabric, but it is preshrunk using tempi-treatment. Knowing that there is no promise of making another jean like this, the detailing takes even the MIJ series to a higher plane: iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese tan shell cordovan leather patch featuring the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, the micro busted outseam, the vintage pink selvedge ID, the selvedge button fly.  Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan. The Easy Guy is a high-rise tapered fit with a relaxed top block and a sharp taper from knee to hem.   Each pair will be delivered in a beautifully made jointed construction pine box. 
 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim 
 100% Cotton 
 
 Made in Japan 
 SKU: 101565606 
 *The on-model images are of a sample. The final product will have contrast thread color, as shown on flat lay product images.
name: MIJ8 - Tokushima Natural Indigo Hand Dyed Intangible Cultural Treasure Selvedge Denim

description_bullet: 17oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Japan,SKU: 101567706
description_paragraph:
The MIJ7 – Yahan Midnight Selvedge is an unsanforized 17oz slubby Japanese selvedge denim dyed to such a deep shade of indigo that it appears black. Indigo rope dyeing is a delicate process of running cotton yarns through two story dye vats quickly enough that the dye cannot penetrate the core of the yarn. Then the yarn dries and is dipped again, dries and is dipped again. The yarns are dipped dozens of times to achieve that raw denim shade. But here, with just a little black dye added, these yarns have been dyed over and over so many times that they appear black. With wear and age, the opposite process occurs. Each layer of indigo chips away revealing dark blues, then medium bright blues, then light blues, then finally the white core of the yarn. This fabric is made to celebrate the full spectrum of variegated indigo shades. The yarns themselves are irregular, slubby, and woven loosely giving the fabric an organic, uneven grain. The denim is unsanforized but tempi treated, which shrinks the fabric but protects the hairiness, grittiness, and raw denim feel. The MIJ7 builds in the unparalleled detailing of the Made in Japan collection: black iron buttons that will rust, copper rivets that will oxidize, raised belt loops that will fade, a Japanese sheepskin leather patch with the “Flower of Carnage” logo, the MIJ maple leaf embroidered onto the back pocket, micro busted outseam, and a selvedge button fly. Dyed, woven, cut, sewn, built in Japan. The Easy Guy is a high-rise tapered fit with a relaxed top block and a sharp taper from knee to hem.

 100% Cotton

description_bullet: 16oz Japanese Selvedge Denim,100% Cotton,Made in Canada,SKU: 101156606
description_paragraph:
The Okayama Spirit 4 is a 16oz Japanese selvedge denim. The Okayama Spirit series has yielded some of the most beloved denim among hardcore Naked & Famous Denim fans. The latest iteration, the Okayama Sprit 4, has an incredible organic grain designed to age beautifully with high contrast fades. The wild streaks and slubs running through the denim come from using yarns that are thick in some places and thin in others, meaning the indigo dye will be absorbed unevenly allowing the potential for a full range of indigos to present themselves with wear. Low tension weaving creates further irregularity in the fabric for an almost handwoven appearance. Unlike previous Okayama Spirits, this fabric is Sanforized, so there should be minimal shrinkage when soaked or washed. Cut, sewn, built in Canada with contrast stitching, a 10oz natural vegetable tan leather patch, and silver metallic buttons and rivets. The Easy Guy is a high-rise tapered fit with a relaxed top block and a sharp taper from knee to hem.
